{#- Trade form error fragment — banner-only. Used when form re-render is not
    applicable (HardCapError, path-aware 404 fallback, trade gone after
    form-GET). For drift-recovery cases (§5.1 cases 1, 2, 3), routes render
    the relevant form template directly with an `error_message` context var —
    the banner appears INLINE inside the form's `<td>`, so the next submit
    replaces both at once (no orphaned banner row).

    `colspan` is caller-parameterized (Codex R2 Major-2): the global
    exception handler in `swing/web/app.py` selects 9 for `hyp-rec-row-*`
    targets (9-col hyp-recs table) and falls back to 8 for every other
    row-swap target (open-positions / watchlist / entry/exit/stop forms,
    all 8-col tables). Defaults to 8 to preserve historical behavior for
    any caller that doesn't pass `colspan`. -#}
<tr class="trade-form-error">
  <td colspan="{{ colspan|default(8) }}">
    <div class="banner banner-degraded" role="alert">{{ error_message }}</div>
  </td>
</tr>
